    <exprreq message="Primary or Secondary Focus (perform) required."><![CDATA[pickexists[cMasPriPe] + pickexists[cMasSecPe] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cMasInspir" name="Inspiration" description="{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Perform 3 ranks.\n\nThe master performer can inspire allies with performances, bolstering them and improving their chances of success. An ally must listen to and observe the master performer for a full round for the inspiration to take hold, and the character must make a DC 15 Perform check. The effect lasts for a number of rounds equal to the character&#146;s Charisma modifier.\n\nAn inspired ally gains a +2 morale bonus on saving throws, attack rolls, and damage rolls.\n\nA master performer cannot inspire himself. The character can inspire a number of allies equal to one half of his master performer level, rounded down (to a minimum of one ally)." compset="CustomSpec" summary="X allies watch 1 rd, +2 morale bon to save, att, &amp; dam for Y rds (DC15 Perform)." uniqueness="unique">
    <comment><![CDATA[xSumm. (Done)

      ~ If we don't have enough ranks in Perform, we're not available
      if (herofield[tMaxPerf].value < 3) then
        var result as number
        result = assign[Helper.SpcDisable]
        endif]]></comment>
    <usesource source="WotL"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="Secondary"/>
