  <thing id="sSorChiSkn" name="Chitinskin" description="{i}Chitinskin{/i} toughens a {b}living{/b} creature&#146;s skin by encasing it within the hardened natural shell of an insect. The effect grants a +1 enhancement bonus to a creature&#146;s existing natural armor bonus for every 2 levels of the spellcaster.\n\nThe {i}chitinskin{/i} fits the target like a second skin, but the shell&#146;s bulk does not allow for the wearing of manufactured armor. The enhancement bonus provided by {i}chitinskin{/i} stacks with the target&#146;s natural armor bonus, but not with other enhancement bonuses to natural armor. A creature without natural armor has an effective natural armor bonus of +0.\n\n{i}Arcane Material Component{/i}: The dessicated shell of a cicada." compset="Spell" summary="+1 enhancement bonus to natural armor/2 levels, can&apos;t wear armor">
