  <thing id="sWizFalFea" name="Falling Feathers" description="This spell creates feathers that fill a 5 foot cube per caster level. The feathers must be in a contiguous pile, though they can be arranged in any shape or piled one atop another. \n\nThe feathers are harmless and do not impede movement, though they can create a safe landing place for falling creatures. \n\nEach 5 feet of depth reduces falling distance by 10 feet for medium or small creatures. Large creatures require a 10 foot cube to reduce it by the same amount, Huge require 15 ft cube, Gargantuan 20 ft, and Colossal 25 ft. Tiny reduce falling distance by 20 feet per 5 ft cube deep.\n\nMaterial Component: A piece of down." compset="Spell" summary="Create a large quantity of feathers to break a fall or obscure  sight">
