  <thing id="sWizRadDar" name="Radiant Dart" description="You create a missile of radiant energy that streaks from your fingertips to strike its target. To successfully strike the target, you must make a ranged touch attack. When the dart strikes its target, it explodes in a burst of brilliant light, dealing 1d4 points of damage and dazzling the victim for 1 round per point of damage taken. If you miss the target, the dart explodes harmlessly.\n\nFor every two caster levels beyond 3rd, you gain an additional dart&#151;two at 5th, three at 7th, four at 9th, five at 11th, six at 13th, seven at 15th, eight at 17th, and a maximum of 9 darts at 18th level. If you shoot multiple darts, you can have them strike a single creature or several creatures {b}(no two of which can be more than 15 ft. apart){/b}. A single dart can strike only one creature. You must designate targets before you check for spell resistance or roll damage." compset="Spell" summary="Create darts that do d4 damage each, and dazzle targets (no save)">
