  <thing id="sDrdFlamWa" name="Flamewave" description="You create a sheet of devouring flames that move away from you at a steady speed, scorching anything in their path. The {i}flamewave{/i} moves at a speed of 30 feet each round, in the same direction indicated at the casting of the spell, which cannot be changed. A {i}flamewave{/i} moves over barriers less than 4-feet high, but it must travel across a solid surface. The {i}flamewave{/i} is 5 ft. high and 1 ft. thick, and 5 ft. wide for every 2 levels of the caster. It ignites flammable substances.\n\nIf the {i}flamewave{/i} passes through a space occupied by a creature, the creature takes 2d6 points of fire damage +1 point of fire damage per caster level (maximum +20). The {i}flamewave{/i} deals double damage to undead creatures.\n\nOnce the {i}flamewave{/i} moves beyond the spell&#146;s range, it automatically winks out of existence. You may also dispel the {i}flamewave{/i} at will.\n\n{i}Arcane Material Component{/i}: A rectangular block of coal or incense." compset="Spell" summary="Wall of flame moves forward 30 ft per round, damaging and setting fires">
